{"add":{"doc":{"id":"f76f7e655387f60307234aae376ce35df181c6c1bed556ee2e4f44784443f785","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Madonna_MDNA_Tour_Milano_14_giugno_2012_3.jpg/220px-Madonna_MDNA_Tour_Milano_14_giugno_2012_3.jpg","previous":[],"after":["Madonna performed \"Masterpiece\" at The MDNA Tour in 2012. It was a part of the second segment of the concert, titled Prophecy, where a mix of joyful songs that \"bring people together\" were performed.[36] The wardrobe during the performance included an all-leather look, a custom design by Hervé Léger and Max Azria, with knee-high boots and a mini fur bolero.[37] After finishing an energetic performance of \"Open Your Heart\", Madonna is joined by Basque musicians Kalakan trio and they perform a Basque song called \"Sagarra Jo\".[38] After that, Madonna sat down to sing an acoustic guitar, fiddle, and beat-based version of \"Masterpiece\", as clips from W.E. appeared in the backdrops.[39] The Kalakan trio backed the singer during the performance, while her dancers accompanied Madonna on stage, dressed as soldiers.[40] The performance of the song at the November 19–20, 2012, shows in Miami, at the American Airlines Arena were recorded and released in Madonna's fourth live album, MDNA World Tour.[41][42]"]}}}